  "prompt": "What are some really good Korean spas in Minneapolis?",
  "response": "Minneapolis has a few excellent Korean spas where you can enjoy traditional Korean saunas (jjimjilbangs) and spa treatments. Here are some highly recommended options:\n\n1. **King Spa & Sauna (Dallas, TX) - Travel Option**  \n   While not in Minneapolis, King Spa & Sauna is a renowned Korean spa chain worth mentioning. If you\u2019re willing to travel, it\u2019s an incredible experience with multiple sauna rooms, hot tubs, and relaxation areas. Keep an eye out for similar spas opening closer to Minneapolis!\n\n2. **The Marsh** (Minneapolis, MN)  \n   While not a traditional Korean spa, The Marsh in Minneapolis offers a holistic wellness experience with saunas, whirlpools, and relaxation rooms. It\u2019s a serene spot for unwinding and may incorporate some spa treatments inspired by Asian traditions.\n\n3. **Lifetime Fitness (Multiple Locations)**  \n   Some Lifetime Fitness locations in the Minneapolis area offer luxurious spa amenities, including saunas, steam rooms, and massage services. While not a traditional Korean spa, they provide a relaxing environment for self-care.\n\n4. **Check for Local Asian Spas**  \n   Some smaller, locally-owned spas in the Twin Cities may offer Korean-inspired treatments or sauna experiences. Be sure to call ahead and ask about jjimjilbang-style amenities.\n\nAs of now, Minneapolis doesn\u2019t have a dedicated traditional Korean spa, but the wellness scene is growing, and new options may emerge! If you\u2019re open to traveling, Chicago has several excellent Korean spas, such as **Chicago Kal-Tel Spa**.",
